Product Description

SONOFF S40 Lite 15A Zigbee Smart Plug with ETL Certified

Compact Size

Compact body designed for wall socket more space reserved.

15A Maximum Current

More durable with 15A maximum current 1800W load.

Extend Communication Distance

Act as Zigbee Router to extend the Zigbee network range.

Remote Control

Forget to turn off the coffee maker? Just take out your phone and turn it off anywhere.

Voice Control

Make your life easier by managing your devices with a simple command.

Set Schedule

Set a timer to turn on or off the connected device as you want.

Sunrise/Sunset Routine

Turn off the lights when sunrise and Turn on the lights when sunset.

Away Mode

Away from home for a long time, turn on the lights as if you were at home.

Bind a Camera

View the device's status and rooms in real-time by adding our camera.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    5.0 out of 5 stars A Smart Choice for Home Automation
    Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
    Verified Purchase
    The SONOFF S40 Lite 15A Zigbee Smart Plug is a fantastic addition to any smart home setup. Its seamless integration with the Home Assistant Zigbee2MQTT system without requiring any modifications is great for any DIY enthusiast. This plug simply works, allowing you to effortlessly control your connected devices through your preferred smart home platform.

    Effortless Integration and Automation:
    What truly sets the S40 Lite apart is its plug-and-play functionality. Simply add it to your Zigbee network and watch it effortlessly integrate with your Home Assistant Zigbee2MQTT system. No complicated configuration or coding is necessary, making it accessible even for those new to smart home technology.

    Unleashing the Power of Connectivity:
    The S40 Lite's ability to interact with other devices takes your smart home to the next level. Create custom automations that trigger various actions based on the state of your connected devices. Imagine turning on a lamp when the smart plug detects a power surge or automatically turning off appliances when you leave your home. The possibilities are endless!

    Reliable and Powerful:
    With a maximum load of 15A, the S40 Lite can handle even your most power-hungry devices. Its compact design ensures it doesn't block adjacent outlets, making it a practical choice for any home. The built-in Zigbee protocol ensures a stable and reliable connection, minimizing dropped connections and ensuring your smart home runs smoothly.

    More Than Just a Smart Plug:
    The S40 Lite is more than just a smart plug; it's a gateway to a world of automation and convenience. Its intuitive design and seamless integration make it a perfect choice for anyone looking to add smart functionality to their home. Whether you're a seasoned smart home user or just starting out, the S40 Lite is an excellent choice that won't disappoint.

    In summary, the SONOFF S40 Lite 15A Zigbee Smart Plug is a winner. Its ease of use, powerful functionality, and ability to seamlessly integrate with smart home platforms make it an excellent choice for anyone looking to upgrade their home automation experience.

  • Roy
    1.0 out of 5 stars not a fan of this product
    Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    Im really disappointed with these smart plugs. I hoped theyd be a valuable addition to my Zigbee network, but theyve proven to be unreliable and frustrating. Every time I try to integrate them, they quickly become unresponsive and disconnect, making them nearly useless. I even attempted to give them away to a friend, only to be met with laughter due to Sonoffs poor reputation.

    Since returning them isnt an option, Im sharing my experience here. Unlike my other Zigbee devices, which stay connected unless their batteries are dead, these plugs frequently drop off the network. Its baffling, especially considering that other devices within 10 feet of these plugs remain stable.

    When they do manage to stay connected, theres a significant issue: the plugs always connect to my coordinator rather than the nearest device. This inefficiency adds unnecessary complications to my setup. Its clear these plugs dont mesh well with my network, and their performance is consistently disappointing.

    After this experience, Im opting to switch to ThirdReality devices. They offer comparable features at a lower price and seem to provide more reliable performance. If youre considering smart plugs, Id suggest looking beyond Sonoff and exploring other brands that offer better connectivity and reliability. If youre interested in smart home products, there are certainly other options that might serve you better.
